<HEADLINE>
COA SELECTS TOP 10 CLASSICAL VILLAGES
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  March  22 (CNA) 03/23/07  11:33:39 (By T.C. Jiang)
</P>
<P>
The Council of Agriculture (COA) has selected Taiwan's top 10
classical agricultural  villages and communities, COA officials
announced Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The announcement came at a ceremony held by the COA. Premier Su
Tseng-chang, COA Chairman Su Jia-quan, and other officials were
present at the ceremony to bestow awards on representatives from
the winning villages.
</P>
<P>
The campaign to choose 10 representative villages is part of a
movement to transform the country's agricultural industry, the
officials said, adding that the winners will receive NT$200,000
prize money and subsidies from the government to further their
development.
</P>
<P>
The Tourism Bureau will also help the winners plan package tours
to promote their villages, the officials continued.
</P>
<P>
This year marks the first time that the COA has initiated such a
contest, the officials noted, adding that the next will take
place in 2009.
</P>
<P>
The winners are Dalian community in the central county of
Changhua, Huasheng Village in the southern county of Yulin, the
Gangbian neighborhood in the eastern county of Yilan, Taian
community in the eastern county of Hualien, Dachingma ginger farm
in the northern county of Miaoli, Yungan Village in the eastern
county of Taitung, Fuchi Hsinglin community in the northern
county of Miaoli, Dayan Village's Seshui community in the central
county of Nantou, Chaomen area in the northern county of Hsinchu,
and Wuhe Village in the eastern county of Hualien.
</P>
